{
  "text": "SwissFEL, like all self-amplified spontaneous emission Free Electron Lasers (SASE FEL), will generate X-ray radiation that varies from shot to shot both in spectrum and intensity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . These variations require a characterization of each pulse with high precision in order to deliver reliable information to the users, enabling them to improve their data quality by normalization with the incoming spectrum on a shot-to-shot basis. Moreover, such a device can provide valuable feedback to the operators for tuning the machine parameters. Since the width of the spectral spikes in a SASE spectrum is linked to the length of the X-ray pulses, high resolution spectral measurements can also serve to determine the pulse duration.",
